00:23:06,944 --> 00:23:08,099
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

276
00:23:10,299 --> 00:23:11,573
There. He’s leaving.

277
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:22,535
Follow him.

278
00:23:23,566 --> 00:23:24,597
Come on. We might lose him.

279
00:23:24,597 --> 00:23:25,620
I know.

280
00:23:48,199 --> 00:23:49,307
Who do you think he’s meeting?

281
00:23:49,442 --> 00:23:50,665
The World Remembers gang?

282
00:23:52,607 --> 00:23:54,833
Maybe he’s afraid of being watched in school.

283
00:23:55,310 --> 00:23:56,587
That’s why he’s meeting them outside.

284
00:23:59,677 --> 00:24:01,677
I think they’re planning the next protest.

285
00:24:03,306 --> 00:24:06,458
Planning the protest in a coffee shop?

286
00:24:07,054 --> 00:24:08,157
Isn’t it weird?

287
00:24:09,739 --> 00:24:10,930
Maybe he’s meeting his lover.

288
00:24:12,851 --> 00:24:13,943
I’m curious now.

289
00:24:15,343 --> 00:24:16,251
Let’s go.

290
00:24:16,548 --> 00:24:17,283
All right.

291
00:24:21,523 --> 00:24:24,223
Welcome to Café for All.

292
00:24:24,223 --> 00:24:25,447
Hi, Aye.

293
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:26,600
Welcome.

294
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:27,540
Hello, Golf.

295
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:28,389
Hello.

296
00:24:28,883 --> 00:24:30,431
The ones you’re meeting are here.

297
00:24:32,097 --> 00:24:32,602
Alright.

298
00:24:32,602 --> 00:24:33,668
Thank you, Golf.

299
00:24:35,224 --> 00:24:36,367
Hi, Mom.

300
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:37,233
Hi

301
00:24:37,654 --> 00:24:38,759
Did I keep you waiting?

302
00:24:38,759 --> 00:24:39,705
Not at all.

303
00:24:42,542 --> 00:24:44,271
Welcome.

304
00:24:47,626 --> 00:24:50,379
Welcome to the café of diversity.

305
00:24:51,107 --> 00:24:51,835
Yes.

306
00:24:52,070 --> 00:24:53,347
That’s a long name.

307
00:24:53,933 --> 00:24:55,284
Your first time here, isn’t it?

308
00:24:55,758 --> 00:24:56,407
Yes.

309
00:24:56,994 --> 00:24:57,853
It is.

310
00:24:58,259 --> 00:25:01,116
The first time is usually exciting.

311
00:25:01,116 --> 00:25:01,870
It’s normal.

312
00:25:02,075 --> 00:25:03,779
You can go pick your seats.

313
00:25:03,779 --> 00:25:06,539
And the staff will take your orders shortly.

314
00:25:06,810 --> 00:25:07,693
Sure.

315
00:25:07,828 --> 00:25:08,538
Please.

316
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:09,924
Thank you.

317
00:25:13,179 --> 00:25:13,937
Wow!

318
00:25:14,608 --> 00:25:16,608
It is indeed the café of diversity.

319
00:25:17,802 --> 00:25:18,524
Right.

320
00:25:18,908 --> 00:25:19,597
Hey,

321
00:25:20,186 --> 00:25:22,491
if we stay on, will we be stereotyped too?

322
00:25:23,206 --> 00:25:24,164
Let’s leave.

323
00:25:24,459 --> 00:25:26,291
Kan, hold on.

324
00:25:26,823 --> 00:25:29,884
If you leave now, you won’t know who Ayan is meeting.

325
00:25:32,255 --> 00:25:33,100
Come on.

326
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,250
There.

327
00:25:40,756 --> 00:25:41,647
Thua.

328
00:25:42,253 --> 00:25:43,350
Hide.

329
00:25:51,009 --> 00:25:52,919
The café is really cute.

330
00:25:52,919 --> 00:25:55,170
It’s so comfortable in here.

331
00:25:57,837 --> 00:25:58,843
It is, Mom.

332
00:25:59,026 --> 00:26:01,026
Glad you and Thuaphu like it.

333
00:26:02,579 --> 00:26:05,499
How are you doing in the new school?

334
00:26:05,664 --> 00:26:06,678
Must be quite tough to adjust.

335
00:26:08,281 --> 00:26:09,628
Not at all.

336
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:14,139
Thuaphu helps a lot.

337
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:18,887
Thuaphu is always a helper.

338
00:26:19,906 --> 00:26:21,567
He really is a great man, Mom.

339
00:26:24,931 --> 00:26:27,473
But he likes to keep what he feels inside

340
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:31,197
just to make other people comfortable.

341
00:26:33,026 --> 00:26:33,812
Aye.

342
00:26:37,275 --> 00:26:39,456
And he’s playing a hero.

343
00:26:39,456 --> 00:26:40,173
Kan,

344
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:41,767
be quiet.

345
00:26:42,286 --> 00:26:43,259
Thua,

346
00:26:44,256 --> 00:26:46,098
whatever you think or feel,

347
00:26:47,868 --> 00:26:49,100
you can talk to your mom.

348
00:26:54,673 --> 00:26:56,063
Is it about Dad?

349
00:26:58,523 --> 00:26:59,859
No, Mom.

350
00:27:00,296 --> 00:27:01,731
It’s nothing.

351
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:04,236
Aye is just rambling.

352
00:27:07,490 --> 00:27:09,030
Ever since I remarried,

353
00:27:09,888 --> 00:27:13,098
I’ve never seen you express any feelings.

354
00:27:13,672 --> 00:27:14,568
I thought…

355
00:27:15,672 --> 00:27:17,792
nothing was wrong.

356
00:27:18,501 --> 00:27:20,230
Nothing is wrong, Mom.

357
00:27:21,385 --> 00:27:22,427
Dad is…

358
00:27:25,091 --> 00:27:26,049
nice to me.

359
00:27:28,173 --> 00:27:31,347
But…it’s his method, isn’t it?

360
00:27:33,477 --> 00:27:35,816
He is so different from your real dad, isn’t he?

361
00:27:40,234 --> 00:27:43,521
I know my son is patient and strong.

362
00:27:49,042 --> 00:27:52,577
But you have the right to express your feelings.

363
00:27:56,552 --> 00:27:58,778
No matter how busy I am,

364
00:28:02,863 --> 00:28:04,583
if it’s about you,

365
00:28:05,848 --> 00:28:07,844
I will always listen.

366
00:28:09,094 --> 00:28:10,304
Do you understand?

367
00:28:10,575 --> 00:28:11,282
I do.

368
00:28:14,909 --> 00:28:16,141
Thank you, Aye,

369
00:28:16,682 --> 00:28:18,682
for finding a way to tell me about this.

370
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:20,902
Of course.

371
00:28:22,835 --> 00:28:26,139
I’m so sorry if I crossed the line.

372
00:28:29,148 --> 00:28:30,186
It’s totally okay.

373
00:28:30,975 --> 00:28:33,789
I know you meant well to Thuaphu.

374
00:28:40,945 --> 00:28:44,571
Should I cancel my appointment so that we can continue chatting?

375
00:28:45,381 --> 00:28:46,726
Please don’t.

376
00:28:46,726 --> 00:28:48,094
You’ve got work to do.

377
00:28:48,452 --> 00:28:50,859
We can continue this at home.

378
00:28:52,890 --> 00:28:54,050
Are you sure?

379
00:28:57,708 --> 00:28:59,090
Please look after him.

380
00:29:00,264 --> 00:29:01,085
Of course.

381
00:29:07,377 --> 00:29:09,377
Thua must have felt very uneasy.

382
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:11,593
Right.

383
00:29:13,670 --> 00:29:15,519
Did he tell you anything at all?

384
00:29:27,656 --> 00:29:28,614
Are you okay?

385
00:29:29,562 --> 00:29:30,965
I am.

386
00:29:33,183 --> 00:29:36,267
I thought it was going to be the end of the world at first.

387
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,004
I’m so relieved now.

388
00:29:45,935 --> 00:29:46,717
Drink up.

389
00:29:47,304 --> 00:29:48,339
They serve really good stuff here.

390
00:29:48,837 --> 00:29:49,669
Agree.

391
00:29:49,850 --> 00:29:50,860
Really good.

392
00:29:54,475 --> 00:29:55,348
Do you come here a lot?

393
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:02,120
Yes.

394
00:30:04,556 --> 00:30:08,769
Someone close to me used to take me here a lot.

395
00:30:10,743 --> 00:30:11,764
Used to?

396
00:30:12,743 --> 00:30:15,416
You guys aren’t close anymore?

397
00:30:23,795 --> 00:30:24,739
He’s dead.

398
00:30:27,291 --> 00:30:28,347
I’m sorry.

399
00:30:30,254 --> 00:30:31,130
It’s fine.

400
00:30:34,829 --> 00:30:36,659
Are you going anywhere after this?

401
00:30:41,265 --> 00:30:42,058
Yes.

402
00:30:48,883 --> 00:30:49,917
Teacher.

403
00:30:50,883 --> 00:30:52,233
May I please talk to you?

404
00:30:52,975 --> 00:30:53,898
About what?

405
00:30:55,686 --> 00:30:57,059
About Ayan.

406
00:30:58,669 --> 00:30:59,432
Hey.

407
00:31:00,669 --> 00:31:02,299
What did you just say to Aunt Waree?

408
00:31:02,488 --> 00:31:03,819
Are you following me?

409
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:06,739
Just like when you and Kan were following me on Saturday,

410
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:07,749
You’re wrong.

411
00:31:08,043 --> 00:31:09,028
I didn’t follow you.

412
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:10,564
Hey.

413
00:31:11,106 --> 00:31:12,282
Just confess already.

414
00:31:15,474 --> 00:31:16,797
Hey, look out!

415
00:33:09,203 --> 00:33:10,430
Remember this, Aye.

416
00:33:11,203 --> 00:33:12,532
You’re special.

417
00:33:13,621 --> 00:33:15,621
Don’t even think you have no one.

418
00:33:16,896 --> 00:33:18,364
You'll always have me.

419
00:33:58,506 --> 00:33:59,587
Thua.

420
00:34:00,869 --> 00:34:01,788
Hey, Kan.

421
00:34:02,878 --> 00:34:04,467
You skipped class too?

422
00:34:05,430 --> 00:34:06,229
Yeah.

423
00:34:06,447 --> 00:34:07,648
Just one day.

424
00:34:10,008 --> 00:34:11,060
Are you here by yourself?

425
00:34:12,438 --> 00:34:13,386
I came with my mom.

426
00:34:13,721 --> 00:34:15,721
But she already left for work.

427
00:34:21,223 --> 00:34:21,809
Come on.

428
00:34:22,825 --> 00:34:23,731
Let’s go for a walk.

429
00:34:25,907 --> 00:34:26,646
Yeah.

430
00:34:32,421 --> 00:34:33,044
Hey.

431
00:34:33,044 --> 00:34:33,865
What?

432
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:35,407
Let’s have some ice cream.

433
00:34:36,979 --> 00:34:37,795
Ice cream?

434
00:34:39,220 --> 00:34:40,373
Why are you in the mood?

435
00:34:40,953 --> 00:34:42,501
Oh, just come.

436
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:50,291
Are you still mad at me?

437
00:34:52,395 --> 00:34:53,505
I’m not mad at you.

438
00:34:56,127 --> 00:34:57,861
Then why don’t you talk to me these days?

439
00:34:58,229 --> 00:35:00,713
Because you’re uncomfortable when I’m around.

440
00:35:01,672 --> 00:35:02,345
I…

441
00:35:02,345 --> 00:35:03,237
I get it.

442
00:35:06,312 --> 00:35:10,246
You don’t like people to judge you just like when they judge me.

443
00:35:23,356 --> 00:35:24,077
Thua.

444
00:35:24,875 --> 00:35:25,574
Yeah?

445
00:35:26,705 --> 00:35:29,769
Whatever problem you have, you can always talk to me.

446
00:35:43,915 --> 00:35:45,359
Damn it! It’s melting.

447
00:35:46,118 --> 00:35:47,111
You should eat fast.

448
00:35:49,166 --> 00:35:50,173
Do it.

449
00:35:50,428 --> 00:35:52,621
Whoa! I can’t stop it now.

450
00:35:53,954 --> 00:35:55,664
Here. Let me wipe it.

451
00:36:05,735 --> 00:36:06,711
Damn.

452
00:36:09,556 --> 00:36:12,466
My mom said my dad still complains about me skipping extra school.

453
00:36:13,348 --> 00:36:14,792
They’re just complaining.

454
00:36:15,206 --> 00:36:16,747
They love you so much anyway.

455
00:36:16,863 --> 00:36:18,404
That’s why they spoil you like this.

456
00:36:28,839 --> 00:36:31,589
Do you think Thua and Aye are so close?

457
00:36:33,948 --> 00:36:35,174
How would I know?

458
00:36:38,854 --> 00:36:41,072
You followed Aye today. What did you get?

459
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:42,627
Did he meet up with The World Remembers?

460
00:36:45,722 --> 00:36:46,604
No.

461
00:36:47,328 --> 00:36:48,772
He didn’t meet anyone.

462
00:36:49,106 --> 00:36:51,976
He just placed a white rose at the edge of the cliff.

463
00:36:53,038 --> 00:36:53,913
Why?

464
00:36:55,944 --> 00:36:57,069
I don’t know.

465
00:36:57,958 --> 00:36:59,958
Does a white rose ring any bell though?

466
00:37:08,315 --> 00:37:09,632
- Teacher Dika.
- Teacher Dika.

467
00:37:10,551 --> 00:37:12,201
I remember now.

468
00:37:12,518 --> 00:37:14,349
Teacher Dika likes white roses.

469
00:37:14,349 --> 00:37:16,542
I saw him have the white rose pot behind his desk until…

470
00:37:16,542 --> 00:37:18,340
Until he moved to Parot school.

471
00:37:23,688 --> 00:37:26,679
How are Aye and Teacher Dika connected?

472
00:37:28,718 --> 00:37:31,081
I used to think they were dating.

473
00:37:31,292 --> 00:37:33,679
And Aye joined our school to get revenge for his boyfriend.

474
00:37:35,475 --> 00:37:37,209
You’ve been watching too many soap operas, Akk?

475
00:37:37,676 --> 00:37:39,361
That plot is really crappy.

476
00:37:40,575 --> 00:37:41,463
Hold on.

477
00:37:42,841 --> 00:37:46,032
What if Teacher Dika was the one who took him to the café?

478
00:37:50,158 --> 00:37:52,400
But Aye said that person was dead.

479
00:37:54,310 --> 00:37:55,199
Right.

480
00:38:20,365 --> 00:38:21,301
Teacher.

481
00:38:27,922 --> 00:38:29,146
May I please talk to you?

482
00:38:29,726 --> 00:38:30,502
About what?

483
00:38:34,494 --> 00:38:35,938
About Ayan.

484
00:38:39,802 --> 00:38:42,044
He’s been behaving lately.

485
00:38:44,255 --> 00:38:47,150
May I please ask you to stop punishing him like that?

486
00:38:48,039 --> 00:38:49,096
What did you say?

487
00:38:50,373 --> 00:38:55,927
I’d like to ask if The Prefect Club can watch his behavior instead.

488
00:38:56,314 --> 00:38:57,157
Can we?

489
00:39:00,756 --> 00:39:03,941
Actually, I don’t want to punish Ayan that badly.

490
00:39:06,478 --> 00:39:08,841
Are you sure you can have him under control?

491
00:39:10,002 --> 00:39:10,827
I am.

492
00:39:11,338 --> 00:39:12,468
I must do it.

493
00:39:16,696 --> 00:39:17,876
He’s your duty then.

494
00:39:19,399 --> 00:39:20,654
Thank you, ma’am.

495
00:39:34,934 --> 00:39:35,572
Hey.

496
00:39:36,805 --> 00:39:38,505
What did you just say to Aunt Waree?

497
00:39:40,763 --> 00:39:42,231
Are you following me?

498
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:45,266
Just like when you and Kan were following me on Saturday,

499
00:39:45,850 --> 00:39:47,243
student prefect.

500
00:39:48,718 --> 00:39:49,518
You’re wrong.

501
00:39:49,615 --> 00:39:50,550
I didn’t follow you.

502
00:39:51,379 --> 00:39:52,236
Hey.

503
00:39:52,768 --> 00:39:53,959
Just confess already.

504
00:39:57,135 --> 00:39:58,505
Hey, look out!

505
00:40:17,863 --> 00:40:18,968
Aren’t you gonna let me go?

506
00:40:22,256 --> 00:40:23,505
You want to hug me?

507
00:40:26,199 --> 00:40:28,030
I just pulled you away from that bike.

508
00:40:28,171 --> 00:40:29,456
I didn’t want to hug you.

509
00:40:30,302 --> 00:40:31,283
Sure about that?

510
00:40:31,797 --> 00:40:32,657
Damn you.

511
00:40:32,657 --> 00:40:34,256
If you’re not thanking me for my help,

512
00:40:34,572 --> 00:40:35,968
stop talking.

513
00:40:38,422 --> 00:40:39,264
Come here then.

514
00:40:40,422 --> 00:40:41,193
To where?

515
00:40:41,362 --> 00:40:42,155
Just come.

516
00:40:42,155 --> 00:40:43,505
Where? I’m making rounds.

517
00:40:43,505 --> 00:40:44,633
Come on.

518
00:40:45,220 --> 00:40:46,155
Let’s go, Akk.

519
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:47,945
I can walk myself.

520
00:41:10,701 --> 00:41:11,552
Don’t.

521
00:41:12,084 --> 00:41:13,233
I can do it myself.

522
00:41:15,270 --> 00:41:16,786
You get used to being my car really fast.

523
00:41:17,295 --> 00:41:18,422
Used to, my ass.

524
00:41:19,969 --> 00:41:21,350
It’s just buckling up.

525
00:41:28,084 --> 00:41:29,093
Where are you taking me?

526
00:41:30,205 --> 00:41:31,196
What are we doing?

527
00:41:31,258 --> 00:41:32,175
Is it far?

528
00:41:32,175 --> 00:41:33,258
What time will we come back?

529
00:41:49,563 --> 00:41:50,497
We’re here.

530
00:41:51,563 --> 00:41:52,847
What are we doing here?

531
00:41:55,787 --> 00:41:56,858
I want a coffee.

532
00:41:57,100 --> 00:41:58,247
Go get it then.

533
00:41:58,505 --> 00:41:59,562
I’ll wait in the car.

534
00:41:59,949 --> 00:42:00,892
You can’t.

535
00:42:01,431 --> 00:42:03,068
Of course, I can. Why can’t I?

536
00:42:40,142 --> 00:42:41,779
What the hell are you doing?

537
00:42:52,773 --> 00:42:58,505
Directed by Tanwarin Sukkhapisit

538
00:42:59,420 --> 00:43:02,121
In my opinion, you’re not fit for that.

539
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:04,319
Someone born with privileges like you won’t understand.

540
00:43:04,319 --> 00:43:07,928
If we let the conflict go bigger, I’m afraid we will eventually fight each other.

541
00:43:10,631 --> 00:43:11,906
What is it, Akk?

542
00:43:11,906 --> 00:43:13,293
Isn’t Teacher Chadok here?

543
00:43:13,409 --> 00:43:15,989
Is the student prefect title that important to you?

544
00:43:15,989 --> 00:43:17,328
It allows me to help this school.

545
00:43:17,418 --> 00:43:20,772
You’re being tamed just to get the reward from those people?

546
00:43:20,772 --> 00:43:24,250
Is it so wrong if I try hard to get the privileges that other people do?

547
00:43:24,250 --> 00:43:25,282
You faggies!

548
00:43:25,282 --> 00:43:26,296
So?

549
00:43:26,296 --> 00:43:29,473
So what if we are? Are you hurt?

550
00:43:29,473 --> 00:43:31,838
Men won’t think too much, Thuaphu.

551
00:43:31,938 --> 00:43:34,518
You’re girlish. That’s why you’re always bullied.

552
00:43:34,971 --> 00:43:38,035
If the curse is back, they might stop.

553
00:43:38,725 --> 00:43:40,096
Let’s not stop fighting.

554
00:43:40,096 --> 00:43:44,328
We will make this school consider changing its obsolete rules.

555
00:43:44,328 --> 00:43:46,387
I will expose what this shitty school did.

556
00:43:46,387 --> 00:43:47,590
I told you to stop!

557
00:43:47,590 --> 00:43:48,665
